@startuml
title Present State -> Solved Unification
left to right direction

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 18
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowThickness 2
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

skinparam package {
  BackgroundColor #f8fafc
  BorderColor #334155
  FontColor #0f172a
}

skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor #334155
  FontColor #0f172a
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #fff7ed
  BorderColor #c2410c
  FontColor #7c2d12
}

package "1. Physical reality to explain" {
  rectangle "Light and radiation\nphotons, interference,\nscattering signals" as RealityLight #dbeafe
  rectangle "Atoms and chemistry\nelectrons, atomic spectra,\nbonding, materials" as RealityAtoms #dbeafe
  rectangle "Nuclei and particle physics\nprotons, neutrons, quarks,\ngluons, collider events" as RealityNuclear #dbeafe
  rectangle "Spacetime and gravity\nmotion, curvature,\nblack holes, cosmology" as RealityGravity #dbeafe
}

package "2. Standard successful formalisms" {
  rectangle "Quantum mechanics\nwavefunctions, operators,\nenergy levels" as FormalQM #dcfce7
  rectangle "Quantum field theory + Standard Model\nfields, gauge bosons,\nfermions, interactions" as FormalQFT #dcfce7
  rectangle "General relativity\nLorentzian metric,\ncurvature, Einstein dynamics" as FormalGR #dcfce7
}

package "3. Current DASHI correspondences" {
  rectangle "Canonical proof spine + theorem owner\nquadratic -> signature -> Clifford -> closure\nOwner: UnifiedPhysicsTheorem\nStatus: repo proved + theorem-owned strong claim\nWhat it currently gives:\n4D-signature-facing formal core" as DashiSpine #fef3c7
  rectangle "Known-limits GR/QFT bridges\nStatus: repo bridge, theorem-backed regimes\nWhat they currently mean:\nregime recovery surfaces, not full recovery" as DashiBridges #fef3c7
  rectangle "Atom/chemistry recovery carrier + bounded atom/wave consumers\nOwner: AtomicChemistryRecoveryTheorem\nStatus: repo packaging/bridge with explicit gates\nWhat they currently mean:\nshared shell/wave recovery carrier,\nfinite wave/phase interfaces,\nnot a final chemistry law" as DashiDynamics #fef3c7
  rectangle "Photonuclear empirical lane\nWhat it currently means:\ncollider measurement sidecar and calibration,\nnot theorem closure" as DashiEmpirical #fee2e2
}

package "3b. Adjacent archive-derived programs" {
  rectangle "DNA-first Agda lane\nCurrent status: local carrier/quotient/UV/\nchemistry/supervoxel/streaming/eigen/channel surfaces\nWhat it currently means:\nreal formal adjacent program,\nnot yet a unification theorem lane" as AdjacentDNA #fff7ed
  rectangle "Brain-side lane\nCurrent status: mainly archive + sibling-repo adjacent\nWhat it currently means:\nstructural/analysis pressure,\nnot localized as a theorem lane here" as AdjacentBrain #fff7ed
  rectangle "Brain-DNA / codec / channel crossover\nCurrent status: partial local interfaces + archive design\nWhat it currently means:\nstorage/channel bridge pressure,\nnot current closure evidence" as AdjacentCrossover #fff7ed
}

package "4. Open gates to a serious unification claim" {
  rectangle "Natural dynamics law\nCurrent status: advanced but blocked\nLanded:\nCanonicalScheduleIndependentNaturalChargeLaw\nBlocked on:\np2-key carrier/schedule bridge\nNext steps:\n1. land the p2-key bridge\n2. reconnect it to canonical bundle transport\n3. only then widen the law beyond the current coarse quotient" as GapDynamics #fce7f3
  rectangle "Conserved physical quantity\nCurrent status: advanced but blocked\nLanded:\nCanonicalScheduleIndependentNaturalChargeLaw\nCanonicalScheduleIndependentNaturalChargeWideningObstruction\nCanonicalScheduleIndependentNaturalChargeNextIngredientGap\nBlocked on:\nno proved widening beyond Gauge × basin × motif\nNext steps:\n1. find a new conserved key that survives CP\n2. prove it is quotient-visible and schedule-stable\n3. tie it back to the natural law" as GapConserved #fce7f3
  rectangle "Continuum limit + realization-independent recovery\nCurrent status: advanced but blocked\nLanded:\nCanonicalToNoncanonicalCoarseRecoveryIdentification\nplus fieldwise gauge/basin/motif equalities\nBlocked on:\nmissing richer MDL-side seam hypotheses\nNext steps:\n1. prove the missing MDL equalities on transported states\n2. reduce coarse-projection dependence further\n3. only then widen to broader carrier recovery" as GapContinuum #fce7f3
  rectangle "Gauge/matter recovery\nCurrent status: advanced\nLanded:\nCanonicalGaugeMatterInterpretableObservableTheorem\nKnownLimitsInterpretableObservableConsumer\nNext steps:\n1. strengthen canonical payload further\n2. recover more physically interpretable fields\n3. upgrade from bundle shape to a finished recovery theorem" as GapGaugeMatter #fce7f3
  rectangle "Atomic and nuclear recovery\nCurrent status: advanced but blocked\nLanded:\nShellDictionaryRecoveryGateTheorem\nAtomicPhotonuclearContactGateTheorem\nChemistryRightLimitsGateTheorem\nBlocked on:\nChemistryRightLimitsInterpretationBlockerSpec\nand atomic owner-cycle cleanup\nNext steps:\n1. break the atomic theorem cycle\n2. land a theorem-side interpretation contract\n3. only then move toward spectra/scattering/chemistry" as GapAtomic #fce7f3
  rectangle "Abstract/canonical seam\nCurrent status: advanced but blocked\nLanded:\nPhysicsUnificationToCanonicalClosureAdapter\nplus coarse recovery identification\nBlocked on:\nricher MDL/refined carrier identification\nNext steps:\n1. keep fieldwise equalities explicit\n2. discharge the richer MDL-side seam obligations\n3. only then tighten abstract/canonical identification further" as GapAdapter #fce7f3
  rectangle "GR + QFT regime recovery\nCurrent status: advanced but blocked\nLanded:\nstronger payload exposure in GR/QFT bridge owners\nplus KnownLimitsInterpretableObservableConsumer\nBlocked on:\nupstream natural/continuum recovery, not bridge packaging\nNext steps:\n1. strengthen upstream recovery payloads\n2. feed them through the known-limits consumers\n3. only then move beyond regime-note strength" as GapRecovery #fce7f3
}

package "5. Target state: solved unification" {
  rectangle "One core theory whose limits recover:\nquantum matter, atoms, nuclei,\nparticle interactions, and gravity\non the right physical regimes" as Solved #bbf7d0
}

RealityLight --> FormalQM : textbook quantum optics
RealityLight --> FormalQFT : photon field picture
RealityAtoms --> FormalQM : atomic structure
RealityAtoms --> FormalQFT : relativistic / field corrections
RealityNuclear --> FormalQFT : particle and nuclear sector
RealityGravity --> FormalGR : spacetime sector

FormalQM --> DashiDynamics : nearest current vocabulary contact
FormalQFT --> DashiBridges : partial bridge target
FormalGR --> DashiBridges : partial bridge target
FormalQFT --> DashiEmpirical : collider-facing measurements
FormalGR --> DashiSpine : Lorentz/signature side relevance

DashiSpine --> GapDynamics
DashiSpine --> GapConserved
DashiBridges --> GapRecovery
DashiDynamics --> GapContinuum
DashiDynamics --> GapGaugeMatter
DashiEmpirical --> GapAtomic
DashiSpine --> GapAdapter
DashiDynamics --> AdjacentDNA : chemistry/contact pressure
AdjacentDNA --> AdjacentCrossover : codec/channel pressure
AdjacentBrain --> AdjacentCrossover : structure pressure
AdjacentCrossover --> GapAtomic : storage/channel/chemistry pressure
AdjacentCrossover --> GapContinuum : adjacent modeling pressure

GapDynamics --> Solved
GapConserved --> Solved
GapContinuum --> Solved
GapGaugeMatter --> Solved
GapAtomic --> Solved
GapAdapter --> Solved
GapRecovery --> Solved

note top of DashiSpine
Strongest current evidence:
formal geometric/closure structure.
Closest to spacetime-formalism language,
not yet to full atom-by-atom physics.
end note

note right of GapContinuum
This is where the public story needed correction:
not solved, no longer "missing from zero",
and now blocked on named seam hypotheses rather than vague future work.
end note

note bottom of DashiEmpirical
Closest current contact with experimental reality:
photonuclear / collider measurement organization.
This is useful, but it is not the same as deriving QCD,
and it is not the only atom/nuclear-facing surface.
end note

note left of AdjacentDNA
These adjacent lanes matter for roadmap truthfulness.
They widen the program beyond the core physics spine,
but they do not upgrade the current repo to solved unification
or to local theorem closure on brain/crossover claims.
end note

note bottom of Solved
This is the bar for saying
"we solved unification" without hedging.
end note

legend right
|= Color |= Meaning |
|<#dbeafe>| familiar physical world |
|<#dcfce7>| standard accepted physics formalism |
|<#fef3c7>| current DASHI correspondence |
|<#fff7ed>| adjacent archive-derived program |
|<#fee2e2>| empirical contact surface |
|<#fce7f3>| missing step / open gap |
|<#bbf7d0>| solved unification target |
endlegend

@enduml
